Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Combine biscuit mix, pepper, and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder in a large bowl. With a fork, stir in milk and cheese until mixture forms a soft dough. Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Combine butter and remaining 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder, and brush on top of biscuits. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.